article.headline: Bryant 70, St. Francis, Pa. 69
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- Frankie Dobbs' jump shot with 1 second left gave Bryant a 70-69 win over St. Francis (Pa.) on Saturday. The Bulldogs (8-16, 6-6 Northeast Conference) led 66-60 with 57 seconds to play before Shannon Umar scored four straight to pull St. Francis within two with 45 seconds to go. Dobbs made two free throws to make it a four-point game 20 seconds later, but Will Felder answered with a jumper for the Red Flash with 17 seconds to go. Umar then put St. Francis (7-16, 5-7) ahead 69-68 on a 3-pointer with 5 seconds remaining, leaving time for Dobbs to get off his game-winner. Cecil Gresham paced Bryant with 19 points and Dobbs finished with 15. Alex Francis added 14 and Matthew Lee 10 for the Bulldogs, who tied the program's Division I record for wins over Northeast Conference opponents, set by the 2008-09 team. Shannon had 16 points for the Red Flash.
